# General Rules

## Code Quality

- TypeScript strict mode, no `any`
- Always handle edge cases, loading states, and errors explicitly
- Named exports for components and functions
- Keep functions small and single-responsibility
- No magic numbers — use named constants

## Structure

- Separate concerns: logic away from UI where possible
- Group related files together
- Consistent naming: PascalCase components, camelCase functions/variables

## Testing

- Write tests for business logic and key user interactions
- Test behavior, not implementation details
- Cover happy path + at least one edge case per unit

## Git

- Commit often with descriptive messages
- Each commit should represent one logical change

## README

- Always maintain a README with:
  - How to run the project
  - Key technical decisions and why
  - What you would add/improve given more time
